{"lang": "go", "code": "package main\n\nimport \"fmt\"\n\nfunc countWords(docs []string) map[string]int {\n\tm := make(map[string]int, len(docs))\n\tfor _, d := range docs {\n\t\tm[d]++\n\t}\n\treturn m\n}\n\nfunc main() { fmt.Println(countWords([]string{\"a\", \"b\"})) }", "question": "Why provide len(docs) as the size hint to make?", "options": ["Avoid repeated rehashing as the map grows; faster on large inputs", "Required syntax", "Cosmetic", "Required to compile"], "correct_idx": 0, "topic": "perf", "subtopic": "map-grow-without-hint", "difficulty": "easy", "explain": "Maps grow by reallocating buckets when load factor exceeds threshold; supplying a size hint avoids multiple rehashes. The hint is approximate and does not constrain capacity.", "sources": ["Go spec"], "iter": 2, "id": "b23affa9b251"}
