{"lang": "go", "code": "package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/hmac\"\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n)\n\nfunc verify(sig, expected []byte, key []byte) bool {\n\tmac := hmac.New(sha256.New, key)\n\tmac.Write(expected)\n\tcomputed := mac.Sum(nil)\n\treturn hmac.Equal(sig, computed)\n}", "question": "Why hmac.Equal vs byte-by-byte ==?", "options": ["Constant-time comparison resists timing attacks and handles length mismatch safely", "Performance", "Cosmetic", "Required by Go"], "correct_idx": 0, "topic": "security", "subtopic": "timing-attack-mac", "difficulty": "med", "explain": "A short-circuit equality loop reveals how many leading bytes matched via response time. Always use constant-time comparison (hmac.Equal / subtle.ConstantTimeCompare) for any secret-derived value.", "sources": ["Go crypto/hmac docs"], "iter": 4, "id": "8b6093dc2a0a"}
{"lang": "go", "code": "package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"time\"\n)\n\nvar safeClient = &http.Client{Timeout: 10 * time.Second}\n\nfunc download(url string) (*http.Response, error) {\n\treturn safeClient.Get(url)\n}", "question": "Why a custom client with Timeout vs http.Get?", "options": ["http.DefaultClient has no timeout and can hang indefinitely on unresponsive hosts", "Performance", "Cosmetic", "Required by Go"], "correct_idx": 0, "topic": "security", "subtopic": "http-timeout", "difficulty": "med", "explain": "http.DefaultClient has no timeout and follows redirects. For any outbound fetch driven by untrusted input, use a custom client with timeout, an allowlist, and a hardened CheckRedirect.", "sources": ["Go net/http docs"], "iter": 4, "id": "f6fc58a2427a"}
